"title": "8462: priority, of God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8462: priority, of god",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture provides examples of individuals who have allowed God to take priority in their lives, and also of those who have allowed something or someone else to take priority.</p>\n<h2>God's glory made a priority</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:9\">MAT 6:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Commands to put God first</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:10\">MAT 4:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:8\">LUK 4:8</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:13\">DEU 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:29\">1CH 16:29</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of putting God first</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:22\">GEN 5:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:24\">GEN 5:24</a> <em>Enoch</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:9\">GEN 6:9</a> <em>Noah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:4\">GEN 12:4</a> <em>Abraham</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:15\">JOS 24:15</a> <em>Joshua</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:3\">2KI 20:3</a> <em>Hezekiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:16-Dan3:18\">DAN 3:16–3:18</a> <em>Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:10\">DAN 6:10</a> <em>Daniel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:29-John3:30\">JHN 3:29–3:30</a> <em>John the Baptist</em></p>\n<h3>Disapproval of not putting God first</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:3\">EXO 20:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:13\">LUK 16:13</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of not putting God first</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:22-Acts12:23\">ACT 12:22–12:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:4\">1KI 11:4</a> <em>Solomon</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:3\">1KI 15:3</a> <em>Abijah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:2\">2CH 25:2</a> <em>Amaziah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:10\">JER 3:10</a> <em>Judah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:1-Acts5:5\">ACT 5:1–5:5</a> <em>Ananias and Sapphira</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:17-Rom16:18\">ROM 16:17–16:18</a></p>\n<h3>Worship commended as the highest human activity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:6\">PSA 95:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:9\">PSA 96:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps99:5\">PSA 99:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:17\">ZEC 14:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:24\">JHN 4:24</a></p>\n<h3>Outstanding examples of worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:14-2Sam6:15\">2SA 6:14–6:15</a></strong> <em>David was prepared to be despised by his wife rather than inhibit his worship.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:6\">EXO 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:3\">ISA 6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:28\">EZK 1:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:10\">DAN 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:38\">JHN 9:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:17\">REV 1:17</a></p>\n<h2>God's kingdom made a priority</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:10\">MAT 6:10</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Commands to participate in the kingdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:33\">MAT 6:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:11-Luke19:27\">LUK 19:11–19:27</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of wholehearted participation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:19\">ACT 26:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:12\">HEB 6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:1-Heb12:2\">HEB 12:1–12:2</a></p>\n<h3>Warning against half-hearted participation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:4-Rev2:5\">REV 2:4–2:5</a></p>\n<h3>Sacrifices for the kingdom advocated</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:29\">MAT 5:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:47\">MRK 9:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:8\">MAT 18:8</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of sacrifices for the kingdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:26\">HEB 11:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:23-2Cor11:30\">2CO 11:23–11:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:21-Phil2:22\">PHP 2:21–2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:30\">PHP 2:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:13\">REV 2:13</a></p>\n<h2>God's will made a priority</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:10\">MAT 6:10</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Conformity to God's will commanded</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:17\">EPH 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:3\">1TH 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:18\">1TH 5:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:20-Heb13:21\">HEB 13:20–13:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:15\">JAS 4:15</a></p>\n<h3>Outstanding examples of conformity to God's will</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:34\">JHN 4:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:38\">JHN 6:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:22-Acts20:24\">ACT 20:22–20:24</a></p>",
